<P>In this &s;haft there are 15 &s;eams of coal, of which on|ly four are workable, viz. the 4th, 7th, 11th, and 12th, making together 4 yds. 1 ft. 7 ins. of w&oacute;rkable coal. If the medium be taken betwixt this and St Anthon's, it will be nearly 6 yards thick of workable coal, from which may be formed&punc;</P>
