</TABLE></P>
<P>From the above &s;tatement it appears, that nearly the fame capital will be required to carry on a farm <HI>in tillage,</HI> at 7s. per acre, that it does one at 26s. per acre:&mdash;There|fore, a farm of <HI>good land</HI> of 100l. per year, will require le&s;s capital than a farm of <HI>bad land</HI> of 100l. per year; and al&s;o, that when the value of the crops in 6 years amounts to no more than 12l. &s;uch lands are improper for arable, and will pay no rent;&mdash;of cour&s;e the mo&s;t profitable mode of employing &s;uch &s;oils, is to let them remain in pa&s;turage.</P>
